OL,3,CHillsborough Law Bill finally laid
OL,4,Cbefore Parliament but what is it?
OL,6,FThe Government has promised that the
OL,7,Flegislation will lead to meaningful
OL,8,Fcultural changes and a public service
OL,9,Fthat truly acts in the public interest.
OL,11,FBut for those who don't, there will be
OL,12,Fcriminal sanctions for the most
OL,13,Fserious breaches, including for
OL,14,Fmisleading the public in a way which
OL,15,Fis seriously improper.
OL,17,FLiverpool's Metro Mayor, Steve
OL,18,FRotheram, who is himself a survivor of
OL,19,Fthe Hillsborough disaster has thanked
OL,20,Fthe Government "for listening and
OL,21,Facting."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/8
